%N A084621 Numbers k such that Fibonacci(k) concatenated with its 10's complement is prime.
%C A084621 Larger values not certified prime.
%C A084621 a(30) > 10^5. - _Michael S. Branicky_, Sep 20 2025; redone for discarding leading 0's. - _Michael S. Branicky_, Apr 26 2026
%C A084621 Any leading 0's in the 10's complement are discarded. - _Sean A. Irvine_, Apr 26 2026
%C A084621 When leading 0's are not discarded, 83 is not a term and 14591 is a term. - _Michael S. Branicky_, Apr 26 2026
%e A084621 31 is a term because Fibonacci(31) = 1346269, 10000000 - 1346269 = 8653731 and their concatenation 13462698653731 is prime.
%e A084621 83 is a term because Fibonacci(83) = 99194853094755497, 100000000000000000-99194853094755497 = 805146905244503 and their concatenation 99194853094755497805146905244503 is prime. - _Sean A. Irvine_, Apr 26 2026
